        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer639641144" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6345510328153216493">I was frankly uninterested in either Vinicius or Ligia, who are cardboard characters, and I couldn’t care less about whether they got together. I know that Quo Vadis was extremely popular in its time (it was published in 1896) and contributed toward Sienkiewicz winning the Nobel Prize for Literature. I also know that Sienkiewicz was capable of creating more interesting characters and writing more exciting scenes. Perhaps the times have just changed too much since this book was written for it to </span>
  <span id="freeText6345510328153216493" style="display:none">I was frankly uninterested in either Vinicius or Ligia, who are cardboard characters, and I couldn’t care less about whether they got together. I know that Quo Vadis was extremely popular in its time (it was published in 1896) and contributed toward Sienkiewicz winning the Nobel Prize for Literature. I also know that Sienkiewicz was capable of creating more interesting characters and writing more exciting scenes. Perhaps the times have just changed too much since this book was written for it to appeal to a wide audience now.<br /><br />See my complete review here:<br /><br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://whatmeread.wordpress.com/tag/quo-vadis/">http://whatmeread.wordpress.com/tag/q...</a></span>
