<span id="freeTextContainer13622312809678203623">I think this is the first book I ever read that upon finishing the last page I immediately wanted to start over again on page 1. A captivating story, well written, with a lot to think about. A fascinating look into Rome and the early Christians. My favorite aspect of the book was the conversion of the main character and the way he changes over the course of the book. I also found myself really loving the character of Petronius and wanting to stop and pray for his salvation! I don&apos;t want to say a</span>
  <span id="freeText13622312809678203623" style="display:none">I think this is the first book I ever read that upon finishing the last page I immediately wanted to start over again on page 1. A captivating story, well written, with a lot to think about. A fascinating look into Rome and the early Christians. My favorite aspect of the book was the conversion of the main character and the way he changes over the course of the book. I also found myself really loving the character of Petronius and wanting to stop and pray for his salvation! I don't want to say anymore because some of my loved ones have not yet finished this book. <br /><br />This is definitely in my top ten fiction books of all time list.<br /><br /></span>
